    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date: January 1, 2025</strong></p>

    <p>
      Insurance Ally respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information.
      This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Personal identifiers (name, email address, phone number)</li>
      <li>Property and claim-related information you voluntarily provide</li>
      <li>Communication data (emails, SMS messages, call records)</li>
      <li>Website interaction data (IP address, browser type, pages visited)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Your information may be used to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Respond to inquiries and provide requested services</li>
      <li>Deliver educational content and support services</li>
      <li>Communicate claim-related updates or reminders</li>
      <li>Send SMS, email, or phone communications you have consented to receive</li>
      <li>Improve our website and services</li>
      <li>Comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. SMS &amp; Communications Data</h2>
    <p>If you opt in to receive text messages:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>We use your phone number solely for communications related to your inquiry or services</li>
      <li>Message frequency may vary</li>
      <li>Message and data rates may apply</li>
      <li>You may opt out at any time by replying <strong>STOP</strong> or request help by replying <strong>HELP</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do not sell or share SMS consent or phone numbers for third-party marketing purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We may share information with trusted third-party service providers solely for operational purposes, such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Messaging platforms (e.g., SMS providers)</li>
      <li>Email and communication services</li>
      <li>Secure data storage and hosting providers</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      All service providers are required to safeguard your information and use it only for authorized purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain personal information only as long as reasonably necessary to provide services,
      comply with legal obligations, or resolve disputes.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Request access to your personal information</li>
      <li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent for communications</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Requests may be submitted using the contact information below.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your information.
      However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Insurance Ally does not knowingly collect information from individuals under the age of 18.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Updates will be posted with a revised effective date.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
